      <hedline>
        <hl1>Progress on Environment?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Francis P Cotter letter suggests Congress may have to re-examine role of nuclear power in reducing greenhouse gas emissions (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You report (front page, Jan. 3) that some electricity-producing utility companies have filed reports with the Energy Department claiming that they have reduced carbon dioxide emissions by operating their nuclear power plants more efficiently.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You report (front page, Jan. 3) that some electricity-producing utility companies have filed reports with the Energy Department claiming that they have reduced carbon dioxide emissions by operating their nuclear power plants more efficiently.</p>
        <p>If the proposal advocated by some senators offering credits to companies now for reductions in emissions that could later be required by law is addressed by Congress, the House would be forced to re-examine the role of nuclear power in reducing emissions.</p>
        <p>FRANCIS P. COTTER  Ponte Vedra Beach, Fla., Jan. 4, 1999</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
